Dear Abinandan,

I have reviewed all three screenshots carefully against the approved M01 
FSD. The UI structure is strong and this is a significant milestone — a 
working SPINRISE transaction screen with a live list, a functional New 
PR form, and a View modal, all rendering real data. The effort is 
acknowledged.

However, before I go through the gaps, I want to name one thing 
specifically. The four-stage workflow bar at the top of the New PR form 
— Draft, Submitted, Approved, PO Created — is exactly the kind of 
SPINRISE-native UX thinking this project needs. The VB6 form had no 
visual workflow indicator. *This addition reflects good product design 
instinct.
*
Now the issues, in priority order.

*Critical — fix before any further testing*

Currency is showing RM throughout — Unit Price, Grand Total, Order 
Summary. RM is Malaysian Ringgit. SPINRISE is for Indian spinning mills. 
Every rupee value in the system must show ₹ (INR). Change this globally 
across all forms, grids, modals, and print templates. This is not a 
cosmetic issue — if this screen were shown to Ashok Textile Mills or any 
customer today, it would raise an immediate question about product 
quality. Fix this first.

*High priority — required per approved FSD*

*Four items are missing from the New PR Item Entry section *that the 
approved FSD explicitly requires.

*Drawing No and Catalogue No are required per line item in the form* — 
FSD Section 12 Rec 28. These fields are in the View modal grid (CAT 
column visible) and in the PR print, but they are absent from the Item 
Entry section of the New PR form. A user cannot enter Drawing No or 
Catalogue No when raising a new PR. Both fields must be added to the 
Item Entry section alongside the existing Item Code, Description, UOM, 
Qty fields.

*Machine No is required per line item*. It appears in the View modal 
grid and in the PR print, but is not in the Item Entry section. Add it.

*Current Stock Quantity must display when an item is selected.* The FSD 
Section 5 requires that on item selection, the system queries current 
stock and shows it against the line item so the requester can see 
whether stock is available before requesting. This is a key business 
rule — the View modal shows STOCK correctly per item, but the entry form 
has no such display on selection.

*Previous Purchase details — Rate, Value, and Date — must auto-populate 
when an item is selected, sourced from the SP*. Again, these display 
correctly in the View modal (LAST RATE column) and in the print, but do 
not appear during entry. The requester needs this information at the 
point of raising the PR, not just in the view.

*Medium priority*

The list view column header shows IT... which is truncated. Expand this 
column to show the full label — Item Count or Items. A truncated column 
header in a production UI is not acceptable.

In the View modal, the CAT column (Catalogue No) is present but the 
Drawing No (DRAWNO) column is missing. Both Rec 28 fields should appear 
together in the modal grid as they do in the print.

The Step 4 label in the workflow bar says PO Created. The VB6 system 
uses Converted as the status. Align this label with the established 
system terminology — change to Converted.

All SUB-COST values in the View modal show 0. Confirm whether this is 
test data or whether the ApproxCost fallback logic implemented in the PR 
print is not yet wired to the modal view. If real PRs, the fallback 
logic (Previous Purchase Rate multiplied by Required Quantity when 
ApproxCost is null) must apply here too.

*Minor*

Cost Centre shows 'sad' as a test value — that is test data and not a 
defect. Clear before any demo.

Item descriptions in the modal show truncated text with ellipsis. Add a 
tooltip on hover to show the full description.

*On overall progress*

*The form is approximately 65 to 70 percent complete a*gainst FSD 
requirements. The architecture, the list-form-modal pattern, the 
workflow bar, and the summary panel are all the right foundation. The 
five gaps above are what separate a working prototype from a 
product-ready screen.

Sasi, please review these gaps with Abinandan today and confirm a 
revised completion date for the fully FSD-compliant M01 PR form. *I need 
that date by end of the day.
*
Regards,
T. Mani
cc: TL-Dev Sasi (review gaps with Abinandan, confirm completion date), 
Mariyaiya (Drawing No / Catalogue No / Machine No field specs from FSD 
Section 4 to be shared with Abinandan).

